response: "{ \"title\": \"Sorting Numbers\", \"description\": \"Write a function that takes as input an array of numbers and returns the same array sorted in ascending order.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef sort_numbers(nums: list) -> list:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `nums` (list): A list of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns a new list with the same elements as the input, but in ascending order.\\n\", \"code\": \"def sort_numbers(nums: list) -> list:\\n    return sorted(nums)\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert sort_numbers([3, 2, 1]) == [1, 2, 3]\", \"assert sort_numbers([-5, -2, 0, 2, 5]) == [-5, -2, 0, 2, 5]\", \"assert sort_numbers([7, 4, 1, 9, 6, 3, 8, 5, 2]) == [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9]\"] }"
